# House Manual Infrastructure

This directory contains only the serving infrastructure (Dockerfile, nginx config, password file).

**The actual Hugo content lives in a separate git repository.**

## Setup

See `../CONTENT_REPOS.md` for instructions on:
1. Creating a separate `house-manual-content` repository
2. Setting up password protection with .htpasswd
3. Structuring your house manual content
4. Deploying to Linode

## Files in this directory

- `Dockerfile` - Multi-stage build (Hugo â†’ nginx with basic auth)
- `nginx.conf` - Web server config (port 8080 with auth)
- `.htpasswd.example` - Example password file format
- `.gitkeep` - This file (keeps directory in git)

Everything else (content/, themes/, config.toml, .htpasswd, etc.) goes in the separate `house-manual-content` repo.

## Important

The `.htpasswd` file with actual passwords should live in the `house-manual-content` repo, NOT here.
Make sure to add `.htpasswd` to `.gitignore` in your content repo!
